    <h2>IT111 Blog Entries</h2>
    <article>
      <h3>Introduction to Computing</h3>
      <p>Introduction to Computing is like learning the basics of a powerful tool. It's about understanding how computers work, from the physical parts (hardware) to the instructions that make them run (software).  We learn how to write those instructions (programming) and how computers handle information (data).  It also covers how computers connect and talk to each other (networks).</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>Information Processing Cycle</h3>
      <p>The information processing cycle is the fundamental way computers work. It's a continuous loop where information is first received from the outside world (input), then manipulated and calculated by the computer (processing), and finally sent back out as results (output).  Some of this information is also saved for future use (storage).  </p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>Introduction to Computer Systems</h3>
      <p>A computer system is like a living organism, made up of interconnected parts that work together to process information.  It consists of hardware, the physical components like the keyboard, monitor, and processor, and software, the programs and instructions that tell the hardware what to do.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="challenge">
      <h3>Lesson Challenge Me The Most</h3>
      <p>The lesson challenge me the most is making a website.</p>
    </article>
